# Assets Insurance Reinsurance Recoverables Paid Outstanding Claims Net Amount

## identifier
de8286

## type
float

## definition
This is the value net of provisions for doubtful debts, as at the relevant date, of reinsurance recoverables in relation to reinsurance contracts for both paid and outstanding claims against the reporting party.
                                                                                                                                                       
Reinsurance recoverables are any amounts due to the reporting party under a reinsurance arrangement that arise from the recognition of Outstanding Claims Liabilities in accordance with capital and prudential standards.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=Assets.Insurance.ReinsuranceRecoverablesPaidOutstandingClaimsNet.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo3.02.05
- period=instant
